TABLE 1 
Supervised contrastive learning is more sensitive to data 
imbalance. Top-1 accuracy (%) on ImageNet-LT with ResNet-50 is 
reported. Implementation details are in supplementary file. " ?" 
represents model is trained with PaCo loss without center learning 
rebalance.

TABLE 2 
Top-1 accuracy on ImageNet-LT for different backbone 
architectures. " ?" denotes models are trained with RandAugment [60]  in 400 epochs. More comparisons with RIDE [29] are in Fig. 1.

TABLE 3 
Performance on Places-LT [37], starting from an ImageNet 
pre-trained ResNet-152 provided by torchvision. " ?" denotes the 
model trained with RandAugment [60].

TABLE 4 
Evaluation with ViT models [64] on full ImageNet and out-of-distribution data. GPaCo models enjoy better generalization ability and stronger 
robustness compared with MAE models. We use their official open-source code for reproduing results of MAE models with 8 Nvidia GeForce 
RTX3090 GPUs. Top-1 accuracy are reported for full ImageNet, ImageNet-R, and ImageNet-S. mCE and rel. mCE are reported for ImageNet-C.

TABLE 5 
Top-1 accuracy on full ImageNet with ResNets. "?" denotes 
supervised contrastive learning with additional operation of image 
warping before Gaussian blur.

TABLE 6 
Top-1 accuracy over all classes on iNaturalist 2018 with 
ResNet-50. Knowledge distillation is not applied for fair comparison. 
We compare with RIDE under comparable inference latency. 
" ?" denotes models trained with RandAugment [60] in 400 epochs.

TABLE 7 
Transfering GPaCo to the semantic segmentation.

Table 5. 
With SimAugment, our ResNet-50 PaCo model achieves 
78.7% top-1 accuracy, which outperforms supervised con-
trastive learning model by 0.8%. Equipped with strong aug-
mentation, i.e., RandAugment
